name: Analog Film Photography By Budi Rahardi

metadata.name: Mother And Son
metadata.description:
This is a photograph of Prambanan temple, once of most popular destination in Yogyakarta - Indonesia.

Besides being magnificent, this place is also wrapped in a very popular folktale about the struggle of Rorojonggrang's love. There are many unsolved mysteries behind the majesty of this temple. From any side you look at, Prambanan temple still looks majestic and elegant.

Technical Detail :
Camera : Mamiya C3
Lens : Mamiya Sekor 105mm F3.5
Film : Ilford Delta 100 Black & White Film
Filter : ND Filter 11 Stop from K&F Concept
Exposure Time : 120 sec
